# Testing

Every implementation must include appropriate tests.

## What to test

| Area | Test type |
|------|-----------|
| Utilities (`src/lib/utils`, feature `utils.ts`) | Unit tests |
| Hooks | Hook / component tests when practical |
| Reusable components (`src/components/`) | Smoke / render tests (React Testing Library) |
| API routes (`src/app/api/`) | Success + failure cases |
| Bug fixes | Regression test covering the fix |

## Conventions

- Tests live beside source: `*.test.ts` / `*.test.tsx` under `src/`.
- Use Vitest + React Testing Library + `@testing-library/jest-dom`.
- Do not snapshot large components.
- Do not assert raw Tailwind class strings unless testing design-system exports.
- Mock `fetch` for BFF/client tests; avoid over-mocking Next.js internals.
- Use `src/test/test-utils.tsx` for BTC feed provider wrappers when needed.

## Definition of Done

Work is **not complete** until all pass:

```bash
npm run lint
npm run build
npm run test
```

## Completion summary (required)

Every implementation must include:

- Tests added / updated
- Commands executed
- Deferred tests (with reason)
